body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Run SymbiYosys on the following file, using the SymbiYosys configuration below:

```
module mcve(i_clk, i_value, o_value);
	input	wire		i_clk;
	input	wire	[1:0]	i_value;
	output	reg	[3:0]	o_value;

	initial	o_value = 0;
	always @(posedge i_clk)
	case(i_value)
	2'b00: o_value <= 4'h1;
	2'b01: o_value <= 4'h2;
	2'b10: o_value <= 4'h4;
	2'b11: o_value <= 4'h8;
	endcase

	always @(*)
	case(o_value)
	4'h0: begin end
	4'h1: assert(o_value == 4'h1);
	4'h2: assert(o_value == 4'h2);
	4'h4: assert(o_value == 4'h4);
	4'h8: assert(o_value == 4'h8);
	default: assert(0);
	endcase
endmodule
```

```
[options]
mode prove

[engines]
smtbmc

[script]
read -formal mcve.v
prep -top mcve

[files]
mcve.v
```

## Expected behavior

At issue is the `default: assert(0);` statement.  If the `4'h0` case statement contains only `begin end`, then the `assert(0)` will fail even the `o_value` is `4'h0`.  If there is any statement between `begin end` this behavior goes away.

This proof should pass

## Actual behavior

The proof fails, with `o_value == 0` at the `default: assert(0)` statement.

